(1) The `.results-table .folder-row td { font-weight: 600; }` rule — the JS never adds a `.folder-row` class to any table row.
(2) The `.breadcrumb .separator { color: #3c3c3c; margin: 0 2px; }` rule — in `renderBreadcrumb` the JS appends a class-less `<span>textContent = '/'</span>` separator.
